The sum of the infinite series is  

\[
\frac{10}{9}+\sum_{k=0}^{\infty}\frac{1}{9}\left(\frac1{10}\right)^k
   =\frac{10}{9}+\frac{1}{9}\cdot\frac{1}{1-\frac1{10}}
   =\frac{10}{9}+\frac{1}{9}\cdot\frac{10}{9}
   =\frac{10}{9}+\frac{10}{81}
   =\frac{100}{81}.
\]

Thus \(m=100\) and \(n=81\) (coprime), so \(m+n=181\).

Answer: 181

